COMPONENT NAME: LKM File to TimesTen (ttBulkCp)
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION This LKM loads flat file data into TimesTen staging area by using the ttBulkCp utility. Call to ttBulkCp is made and a specific log file is created. Oracle recommends looking at this file in case of error.
REQUIREMENTS The source file must be accessible by the ODI agent executing the interface. The agent machine must have TimesTen daemon process running and ttBulkCp be in the PATH. All mappings need to be on the staging area. All source fields need to be mapped, and must be in the same order as the target table in TimesTen.
LIMITATIONS Source files must be delimited format.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
The name of the data file(s).
If no filepath is specified, current work directory will be used.
If not specfied, it will be the data file appended by .err. If the file already exists, overwrites it.
If not specfied, it will be the data file appended by .err. If the file already exists, overwrites it.
If not specfied, it will be the data file appended by .log. If the file already exists, overwrites it.
Specify the maximum number of rows
Specify the maximum number of rows. If 0, the ttBulkCp only connects, then returns.
error level for exceeding the scale

This error can be generated for a decimal value whose scale exceeds the maximum scale of its column or for a TIMESTAMP value with more than 6 decimal places of fractional seconds.
error - Specifies that ttBulkCp should not insert a row containing a value that exceeds its maximum scale into the table and that it should place an error into the error file. warn - Specifies that ttBulkCp should right-truncate the value to its maximum scale before inserting the row into the table and that it should place a warning into the error file. ignore - Specifies that ttBulkCp should silently right-truncate the value to its maximum scale before inserting the row into the table.

This error can be generated when a CHAR, VARCHAR2, NCHAR, NVARCHAR2, BINARY or VARBINARY value is longer that its maximum column width.
error - Specifies that rows containing long string or binary attributes should not be inserted into thte table and that an error should be placed into the error file. warn - Specifies that long string or binary attributes should be truncated to the maximum column length before being inserted into the table but that a warning should be placed into the error file. ignore - Specifies that long string or binary attributes should be silently truncated to the maximum column length before being inserted into the table.

This error can be generated when a real, float or double attribute underflows. Underflow occurs when a floating point number is so small that it is rounded to 0.
error - Specifies that rows containing a real, float or double value that underflow should not be inserted into the table and that an error should be placed into the error file. warn - Specifies that 0.0 should be inserted for real, float or double attributes that underflow, but that a warning should be placed into the error file. ignore - Specifies that 0.0 should be silently inserted for real, float or double attributes that underflow.
Set the comment character in the input file. "none" disables the use of comments in the input file.
Specify the encoding to be used for NCHAR and NVARCHAR values. Valid values are UTF8, UTF-8 or ASCII.
Specify whether DATE values include date+time or just date. Valid values are date, timestamp.
Specify the first row to be inserted.
Specify the last row to be inserted.
Specifies that ttBulkCp should checkpoint the data store after every <numTrans> transactions.
Specifies that ttBulkCp should commit after every <numRows> successful inserts.

import java.lang.String import java.lang.System import java.util.logging import os import string import subprocess as sub import sys
connString ="<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_JAVA_URL")%>" print connString if string.find(connString, 'direct') == -1: useDirect = 0 else: useDirect = 1 if string.find(connString, '=') == -1: useDSN =1 else: useDSN = 0 words = string.split(connString, ':') dsn_connstr = words[3]+ ";UID=" + '<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%>' + ";PWD=" + '<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_PASS")%>' target = r'''<%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "A")%>''' target = string.replace(target,'"','')
srcfileformat = "<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_FORMAT]", "", "")%>" delim = "<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[SFILE_SEP_FIELD]", "", "")%>" first_row_from_file= <%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_FIRST_ROW]", "", "")%> first_row_from_file = first_row_from_file+1 src_file = "<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[RES_NAME]", "", "")%>"
quoted_value = 1 <% if (odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[FILE_ENC_FIELD]", "", "").length()==0) {%> quoted_value = 0 <% } %>
temp_dir2 = r'<?=java.lang.System.getProperty("user.home")?>' os_name = "<?=java.lang.System.getProperty("os.name")?>" s = os_name[0:3]
if s == "Win": temp_dir = temp_dir2 + "\\" else: temp_dir = temp_dir2 + "/"
# # ttBulkCp Options # data_file = r'<%=odiRef.getOption("DATA_FILE")%>' log_file = r'<%=odiRef.getOption("LOG_FILE")%>' error_file = r'<%=odiRef.getOption("ERROR_FILE")%>'
if data_file == "": data_file = r'<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[WORK_SCHEMA]/[RES_NAME]", "", "")%>' output_dir = temp_dir if log_file == "": log_file = output_dir + src_file + '.log' if error_file == "": error_file = output_dir + src_file + '.err'
max_errors = "<%=odiRef.getOption("MAX_ALLOWED_ERRORS")%>" decimal_overflow_error = "<%=odiRef.getOption("DECIMAL_OVERFLOW_ERROR")%>" str_overflow_error = "<%=odiRef.getOption("STR_OVERFLOW_ERROR")%>" float_underflow_error = "<%=odiRef.getOption("FLOAT_UNDERFLOW_ERROR")%>"
comment_char = "<%=odiRef.getOption("COMMENT_CHAR")%>" encoding = "<%=odiRef.getOption("ENCODING")%>"
date_mode = "<%=odiRef.getOption("DATE_MODE")%>" date_format = "<%=odiRef.getOption("DATE_FORMAT")%>" time_format = "<%=odiRef.getOption("TIME_FORMAT")%>" timestamp_format = "<%=odiRef.getOption("TIMESTAMP_FORMAT")%>"
first_row = "<%=odiRef.getOption("FIRST_ROW")%>" last_row = "<%=odiRef.getOption("LAST_ROW")%>" cp_policy = "<%=odiRef.getOption("CP_POLICY")%>" txn_policy = "<%=odiRef.getOption("TXN_POLICY")%>"
if useDirect == 1 or s == "Win": loadcmd = '''ttBulkCp -i''' else: loadcmd = '''ttBulkCpCS -i'''
#=========================== # load() #=========================== def load(): # Check if the file is delimited otherwise raise an error if srcfileformat == 'F': raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-FILE-LKM-10000", "ODIKM-FILE-LKM-10000: This LKM works only with delimited files")
global loadcmd
if s == "Win": loadcmd += ' -s' + delim else: loadcmd += ' -s' + '\'' + delim + '\'' if cp_policy <> "": loadcmd += ' -cp ' + cp_policy loadcmd += ' -e\"' + error_file +'\"' if max_errors <>"": loadcmd += ' -m' + max_errors if str_overflow_error <>"": loadcmd += ' -t ' + str_overflow_error if float_underflow_error <> "": loadcmd += ' -u ' + float_underflow_error if txn_policy <>"": loadcmd += ' -xp ' + txn_policy if comment_char <>"": loadcmd += ' -C' + comment_char if date_format <> "": loadcmd += ' -dformat ' + date_format if time_format <> "": loadcmd += ' -tformat ' + time_format if timestamp_format <> "": loadcmd += ' -tsformat ' + '\'' + timestamp_format + '\'' if first_row <> "": loadcmd += ' -F ' + first_row else: loadcmd += ' -F ' + str(first_row_from_file) if last_row <>"": loadcmd += ' -L ' + last_row if encoding <> "": loadcmd += ' -N ' + encoding if quoted_value == 0: loadcmd += ' -Q 0' if decimal_overflow_error <> "": loadcmd += ' -S ' + decimal_overflow_error if date_mode <>"": loadcmd += ' -dateMode ' + date_mode if useDSN == 1: loadcmd += ' '+dsn_connstr else: loadcmd += ' -connStr ' + '\"' + dsn_connstr + '\" ' if s == "Win": loadcmd += ' '+target+' '+data_file else: loadcmd += ' \''+target+'\' '+data_file
print loadcmd odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, loadcmd)
pro = sub.Popen(loadcmd,stdout=sub.PIPE,stderr=sub.PIPE,shell=True) (pout,perr)=pro.communicate() log=open(log_file,'w') log.write(pout) log.write(perr) log.close() #if pro.returncode==1: # raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-STDKM-10011", "ODIKM-STDKM-10011: Load Error. See '{0}' for details",[log_file])
Report the number of loaded rows

import re
# Init Vars nbRows = 0 nbIns = 0 nbBad = 0 strprt = "" c = 2
src_file = "<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "[RES_NAME]", "", "")%>" temp_dir2 = r"<?=java.lang.System.getProperty("user.home")?>" os_name = "<?=java.lang.System.getProperty("os.name")?>" s = os_name[0:3] if s == "Win": temp_dir = temp_dir2 + "\\" else: temp_dir = temp_dir2 + "/"
log_file = "<%=odiRef.getOption("LOG_FILE")%>"
if log_file == "": log_file = temp_dir + src_file + '.log'
f = open(log_file, "r")
try: lines = f.readlines()
while c < len(lines): line = lines[c]
if line.strip().find("total") <> -1: nbRows = int(re.findall("\d+", line)[0]) if line.strip().find("not inserted") <> -1: nbBad = int(re.findall("\d+", line)[0]) if line.strip().find('rows inserted') <> -1: nbIns = int(re.findall("\d+", line)[0]) c+=1 strprt = "\n\tReads:\t%s\n\tIns:\t%s\n\tBad:\t%s\n" % (nbRows, nbIns, nbBad) #print strprt odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, strprt) odiRef.setNbRows(nbRows); odiRef.setNbErrors(nbBad);
finally: f.close()
